column7: Review

This is a brand new Culver's in Lansing, Michigan. The food was outstanding, the best I have had at any Culver's, which is generally very good. Even though there were many patrons, our food arrived quickly and was the perfect temperature. The cheese curds were excellent, both squeaky and pully.  I had a butter burger. My son had chicken tenders. The portions were generous. The staff was very polite and attentive.  Even a visiting Franchisee from Georgia, Ali, was fully engaged and welcoming.
And, of course, the root beer is wonderful.

I highly recommend this Culver's for a dinner treat and a dish of frozen custard. Pricing is a little more than fast food, but worth it.

This is our local Culver's for South Lansing. Having just opened, there is a lot of clientele.  But the food came just as fast as ever. Good temperature.  The butter burger was tasty.  The cheese curds wonderful.  My son had chicken tenders, and these were very good. Ali, visiting as a Franchisee from Georgia was so attentive and engaged.  The employees looked happy to be there.  And the frozen custard with the cashews was amazing!  I think I have another post somewhere on this but it is worth taking the time to talk about.  If there is any shortcoming it is how full the parking lot is.  That is a good sign of a new restaurant. Enjoy!

This Culvers is one of the worst Culvers ive experienced in awhile.  The person working drive thru absolutley hated her job and you can tell.  Before we even got to the windoes it took almost 11 minutes.  From the time we pulled in to the time we got our food we waited a total of 25 minutes.  The person working drive through seemed like she was depressed.  I felt bad as she mumbled and didnt make eye contact.  Clearly something was going on and clearly this Culvers needs to do something better to motivate their staff.  I would not recommend this place, nor will i ever come back.

Always been one of my fvaorite authentic go to ice cream places when im craving an original soft creamy smooth freshly made ice cream custard. Been going thr on off since 8 yrs now..they also have tasty soups & burgers n other sides.ive never tried their burgers but their fries r decent.price is decent. Average not too expensive. Last 3 days i was going everyday foe the flavor of the days. So far i did like red raspberries, n double strawberry n todays the new flavor of the month creamy lemon crumble!!!

My family loves Culver's but this location needs some help to get on par. The guy taking our order talked fast and quiet. We had to go over the order with him several times before he rang it up correctly. When he brought out or food, I noticed part of my wife's order was wrong, and I let him know. He walked back behind the counter then came back to say he needed to take back the item that was wrong. He did so, and promptly through the item in the trash on his way back behind the counter. It then took another 10-15 minutes for them to bring out the correct item for my wife. None of the staff were positive or friendly about anything. Thankfully the food was as good as usual which is the only thing that saved this from a 1 star.

Also, I noticed the manager was leaving just as we arrived, and by his demeanor, you could tell he knew his staff was struggling. He did not offer to stay and help. He did criticize the staff on the way out though...

The drive thru, order taker, was so awesome! She was positive and happy. Very friendly women. I love this Culver's.  I even called before I went and the girl on the phone was just as upbeat and positive. And the girl handing out the food to our cars, her too!! Great customer service ladies! And tell the cooks thanks, it was good!

I went through the drive through and they took awhile but that is to be expected when going to Culver’s but THEY FORGOT MY TOP BUN?!?? And I tried to call but constantly got sent to voicemail mail... so hopefully somebody sees this.

I love this Culver’s and come here often. My one complaint... stop taking more orders than you can fill and then telling people to pull forward... Waited 25 minutes In line- no big deal, lots of customers. Then I had to wait 20 minutes past when I paid, only to get an incorrect order that took another 15 minutes to correct. It seems like they could focus on current orders rather than getting as many people past the cashier as fast as possible and then slowing way down when it comes to actually bringing food out.

Seriously? I can not imagine a worse experience. Waited in line for literally 25 minutes, and the two sandwiches we ordered with an extra side of tartar sauce came with no sauce at all.
Called them twice to see if we could skip the massive line and just get our sauce....no answer on the phone.
Absolute fail. Worst fast food experience I have had in years.

I always order a burger with mustard and extra mayo only, most places won't put the extra mayo on. Culver's did and it was so good. Also upgraded to pretzel bites instead of fries. They are really good as well. It was a beautiful day to sit outside. I will recommend taking some antibacterial wipes to wipe your table down as all outside were dirty. We still enjoyed our lunch just laid napkins down.

One customer ahead of us in drive thru, got a small cup of custard, took like 10 minutes before she got her order.  We got 1 concrete.  Pulled up to window, worker sat with her back against the window, ignoring us.  Then finally opened it and asked what we had ordered (should have known).  Then about 10 minutes later it was brought to our car.  At 9 pm, it wasn't busy!  We waited.a total of 20 minutes for ONE item.  Worst customer service I've ever had at a Culver's.  Glad I was just passing through town, and dont have to return.

I've been here twice and both times I have been very happy with the service and with the food. The girl taking orders is very friendly and knowledgeable. And the wait times aren't that bad considering they make every burger to order. The prices are also quite reasonable. They've made a regular out of me.

This place can be good or bad, I've had both experiences, sometimes the meat is cold and dry, definitely undesirable while other times it's what you would expect meat to be  hot and juicy. The frozen custard on the other hand is always exceptional you get what you are expecting.

Went to Culver's after a movie. They were still open after 8 pm and had dining inside. Our food was good, hot, and fast. I ordered fries extra crispy and they were not extra crispy.  Otherwise I would have given them a 5. Dining room was clean and appeared to have been recently santized.

This was a terrible experience, the order was incorrect the sides not correct I was not asked about any sauces, my food was dry and bland, I was asked to pull ahead and did not know how far to pull ahead I just went up far enough for the other cars to leave the drive though.  Trying to order was also a task the person taking the order was able to be heard. However I will the the lady that brought out the food was very nice and professional. I just wish I would have checked the order before I left.

Oh Culver's, how I love thee. My food is always good, somehow my fries stay good on the drive home. There is always a line so try to use it as a time to relax for a bit. These folks are working so hard, I always slip a couple bucks to whoever brings my food out.

Good food. Pretty clean. Bathroom faucet in the men's room didn't work correctly, just drizzled.  Service was good and employees were friendly.
https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP5b9nLSATsy3lGACsaxPXKolLiaL75ZIy85mTw=w150-h150-k-no-p
https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP5b9nLSATsy3lGACsaxPXKolLiaL75ZIy85mTw=w150-h150-k-no-p

I’d never been there before, and the only reason i went is because i had a gift card. I’m going thru some stuff, and i don’t know what happened really, but i had an anxiety attack trying to order, and the poor kid at the register couldn’t get the gift card to work and I’m was obviously making him super uncomfortable. Meanwhile, I’m just wishing i would drop dead on the spot because i know i look insane. Someone (a young woman, brown hair i think?) was called over to help with my order, but there was still some issue with the gift card. Im not entirely sure, at that point i was just trying to get out of there with out embarrassing myself further. She ended up bringing me my malt and gave me a coupon for a meal to come back. I just wanted to say thank you and I’m sorry to both her and the young man who took my order originally. I also just wanted to briefly explain myself so neither of them thought they had done anything to upset me. I’m SUPER embarrassed and am very thankful for their kindness.

So good the only thing left one plate was half a pickle.Food was freshly made and perfectly cooked.We dined in and the entire staff was so nice and professional.The location was very clean and everyone seemed to be enjoying there meals.A-1 service.Just as good every time.

I'd never been to Culver's before and I mentioned that to the young man at the register hoping he could maybe give me some suggestions but instead he just stood there annoyed and I ended up with a burger combo that I could have got from any number of fast food places. My husband just got some fries and water and it came out to $14. The lobby is clean so yay for them.

I come here all the time and service is usually great I only get a messed up order every once in awhile. I do have to say please stop interrupting me while I’m ordering, I get it you’re trying to be fast and efficient but it’s quite rude let me finish my order first and then you read it back to me.

Incredibly busy and super slow.  Plus once order was received, it was missing an item.  Thankfully I  checked it before pulling away. I understand the worker shortage and accounted for that situation as to the wait time.  However I cannot excuse missing  items.  Not a deal breaker because the food has been acceptable.  Lesson is to check your order before leaving!

Pretty tasty, hot, fresh and cooked perfectly.  The fries are always piping hot and crispy. The staff have always greeted us with smiles and suggestions if they have items to pitch.  Not a bad location, the views out the windows are nice while you catch as bite with friends or family.

The girl that took our order didn’t even hear half the things we said. When we got our food and realized half of it wasn’t on the receipt we asked about it and they said they could retake our order. They didn’t give my kids their chocolate milks. Made my daughter cheeseburger with nothing on it but pickles. We tried to talk to them and they just dismissed us like it didn’t matter. Will never eat here again.
I absolutely  LOVE Culver's ! Quality food. I was charged extra for tomatoes, but I wasn't  made aware of this before ordering. I  went through the drive-thru.

Had to remind them we needed our 3rd drink, my burger was suppose to have everything on it & it only had ketchup, we had 3 drinks & 3 ice creams & they didn't give us a drink holder for any if it, didn't fill our root beer & gave us our ice cream first so it melted while we waited for our food (drive thru).

Service was mediocre. The drive-thru attendant was rude and having side conversations. I asked for the flavor of the day which was cookie dough and basically got vanilla ice cream with cookie dough on top. The ice cream does not taste the same as other Culver’s. It tasted like freezer burn ice cream.

Order was wrong, food was missing, Owner refuses to take calls or call back. Corporate claims there is nothing they can do because "Charles" is an independent owner. Called store the day it happened: they wanted me to drive an hour back to the store with the food that was missing to begin with in order to get a refund. Pretty funny how the shift managers all claim they're owners when you call them, either Corporate Culvers isn't paying attention to this place or they simply don't care. Made a stop passing through Lansing, next time I won't.

Rude at drive through, not helpful at all .. for this being my first visit at Culver's, it will most certainly be my last. Very disappointed and offended that I would be scoffed at for ordering four kids meals.

We absolutely ❤️ Culver's! We can't seem to go anywhere without everyone knowing my fiance, so we went in and it was a great experience. We were greeted at the door with a smile and a "Welcome to Culver's". Love the frozen custard and the butter burger. 😋 YUMMY!
I generally really love a good butter burger.  This location needs to learn how to use salt and pepper.  Hot fries though!!!!
I enjoy Culver’s often I really like the fast service when it comes to the food, they should definitely come up with a different process with they’re ice cream, mult, freeze drink making system

Do you like waiting 40 minutes for the wrong or incomplete order, then this place is for you. Not only are they slow, but they're also incapable getting your order correct. The place is rampant incompetence from management on down. This has happened to me every visit. I could understand one bad visit. I decided to give them a second chance after the worst experience I'd ever had at a fast food restaurant. That was my mistake. I heard that they were doing somewhat better. Guess what??? They aren't.
Never eat here, I don't think this is necessarily true of all Culver's locations. But South Lansing Culver's is the WORST! I wish to give it negative stars. The real review is -793 stars.

Visited this establishment on November 3, 2022. Drive through order #92. Ordered a butterburger cheese meal, onion and mayo only. After waiting between 15 and 20 minutes for my order finally got it. But no fries in the bag. Went back but inside got my fries. Came back to car to eat just to notice my burger had EVERYTHING on it. My pretzel bites was lukewarm. If my food was made fresh it all should have been much warmer than recieved. I called to complain and the person named Ell I belive took my call it was a male. Told me to bring back the food and they would make my meal fresh. Told him I just spent 20 min in drive through and getting my fries I don't have the time as I was in my lunch. I didn't have time for this. Shouldn't have taken more than 10 minutes to get my food once paid for and began waiting. First time.visiting this establishment and I don't think I'll be back.

Went for a turtle sundae and strawberry shake. 3 people ahead of us no big deal but 20 minutes waiting and 3 orders BEHIND us got served before us.
Got attitude from the manager because we asked for our money back and did not get our ice cream. Thanks for the experience I'm sure the Culver's family are proud of the management attitude.

Cheese curds don't include a dipping sauce? Prices have gone way up and EVERYTHING cost extra! This location is under new management and prices have gone sky high... Rude employees to top it off. My previous visit both burgers were raw in the middle... Avoid this location, all others Culver's in the area are awesome and care about their customers, not this one. I sure hope corporate steps in before this location goes out of business and hurts the Culver's  brand.

I would not recommend this location to anyone. They were rude and talking about how we ordered our food with the headset still on so we could hear them. They did not include our sides that we ordered and nothing was put on our burgers except cheese when we clearly asked for them to be topped with everything that comes on them. My burgers were also burnt to a crisp and the cheese curds were super old. I was missing around $15 worth of my $50 order. When I called to let management know their phone lines were shut off so that nobody is able to reach anyone.

Placed an online order. Got home and found out they shorted me a fry. Seems like a simple issue, refund the few dollars for the fries and no harm no foul. They refused to refund my money AND accused me of lying over the phone... about an order of French fries. They claimed that they could only refund money in person... Even though I ordered and paid online.
In a nutshell it's overpriced, mediocre food coupled with horrible customer service. Find someplace else to eat.
Employee take order in drive thru was so pleasant! Drive thru was busy, but she really made my day

Food is always the same. Last two yimes we have been to this particular resturant they have forgot our ice cream order. I have had to go ask for its status.
This visit I was there with my two younger children and heard some LOUD explicit language being said by the employees it was very disturbing.

There's Always a line, Because the Food Is Delicious! Culver's burgers tasts like homemade❤😋They have the best fries, and we prefer their custard over every other business's ice cream.
Our 2 favorite things:
1)the kids meal offers enough to satisfy just about anyone & we love the entre options.
2)they have flavor of the day custard (different @ each location) as well as they're usual flavors/varieties.
Considering the portions/cost, Culver's offers both Quality + Quantity.
Every once in awhile, they forget something & we have to go back around or run inside, they make it right, tho.

Food was cooked perfectly. I’m really picky about how my fries are cooked. Everything came out in a timely manner. Donna is very kind and sociable. She only works in the dining are a few hours each week.
Always great food. Friendly & helpful staff. Never disappointed
Staff was very friendly! I came in with a big group that included 7 children. One staff member in particular made us feel welcomed, she was patient and very outgoing!

This place gets it right ..... great food ...service was even better.... fries were some of the best I've had at any fast food place and the  Double Burger with bacon was very good 👍 😋
Came back to try the walleye dinner...very very good  The fish fillets were excellent very big fish with highly recommend the 2 piece dinner to anyone this is the real deal real walleye Fish and big ..... 3 piece dinner enough for 2 people with a small fries.... The fish sandwich was also very good with added cheese....

Long wait depending on what day and time you come, (Google has a detailed information on when is best time to come, more accurate than my guesses).  It's similar to Wendy's (fresh never frozen), but Wendy's cook's hamburger patties in groups ahead of time, ready instantly, sometimes they get overcooked, if nobody buys a Wendy's hamburger they get burnt and tossed into a pile for tomorrow's Chili.  Culver's is cooking your meal fresh, so there is a longer wait, however the fries are always hot & crispy, and the hamburgers are always juicy with melted cheese.  None of those gross fastfood hamburgers that weren't hot enough to melt cheese. They have better ice cream products (with egg), and fried cheese curds! But be careful they're killing us with heart disease and diabetes!  Culver's has one of the best fish sandwiches or get a few for a Fish & Chips basket. It's not pretty because it's a true fresh fish filet, not a frozen processed square of unknown fish meats.  Personally I love the melts, served on buttered toast instead of a bun.  Buttered toast, beef, cheese, roasted onions, etc is an amazing way to raise my cholesterol, yum!

Good as a treat after going shopping at Meijer. Greasy but amazing and the pretzel bites are so good

I was asked to pull ahead after i paid but didn't give me my drink. Took a while to get my order and I didn't get the burger I oredered nor the drink. The young man ran in to get the drink. No napkins in the bag. The burger was overdone and charred. I ended up eating only half. Disappointed this time.
Culver's is the best fast food in Lansing period. It is always fresh and hot because they make it once you order. It is never a long wait and the young staff is super polite and helpful!

The fish oozed a tablespoon of oil.  It was a disappointment even without considering it was like $14.00.   if the oil is hot enough when you drop it, that won't happen. Procedures and processes, Culver's. Do better!

Dayton did a great job in resolving my problem with my order. He took the initiative to "911"  my re-order. Background. In the drivethrough I ordered a butter cheeseburger, large malted and onion rings. When I received the burger, i noticed it had no condiments. Being new to Culver's I didn't know I needed to list all the condiments and fixings. So I took the burger back inside to the counter and spoke to Dayton asking if I could have some pickles, onions, lettuce, ketchup and mayo for my burger and I said I'd put them on myself. He said, "No need for that. I am happy to make a new burger for you. How do you want it?"  I described the fixings I wanted and he then said, "Great. I'll even throw in some fries for your trouble."  Then he went to the kitchen and I heard him say to "911" my order. I really appreciate Dayton's initiative and going above and beyond to fix my problem.

Excellent service and really good food. Burgers, sandwiches, fries, onion rings, pretzel bites and amazing desserts made with custard

Great food! The drive thru line wait was about 10 minutes.
Sandwich ok. Drive through, no napkins given. This is a red flag for me.

If you want a concrete mixer that isn’t melted, I suggest going to a different location. Came through and got two concrete mixers, both not filled completely, melted so it was more like a soft drink, and there was barely any toppings in each mixer. Got caramel in one and there was barely any of that. Didn’t wait very long so I’m not sure why they were melted. Tried calling the store but was sent to voicemail. I’ll be calling tomorrow to address this with a manager 😊.
Decent fast food... Kind of $$ but better than McD!
This is the best Culver's around! Everyone is always so nice here. A girl with a name tag reading India brought my food out and was so sweet and helpful! Only Culver's I'll visit!

After giving this location 3 chances now, this review needs to be shared. I order a very simple concrete mixer... chocolate base, pb sauce and oreos.. that's it and it has always been made wrong. First time it was made I was given a chocolate base and only oreros, second was chocolate base and only pb, and just now I asked for a chocolate base, pb sauce and pb cups, and got vanilla base chocolate sauce and pb cups.....

When I go inside, as we usually order from the drive thru, I am treated like it's no big deal. It has never been addressed as " I am sorry and do apologize, how can we fix this for you" or anything along those lines. The staff whips it out of my hand, and when given my correct order its "here ya go" and just walks away. No apology and definitely a very weak customer service experience. Also, we have noticed the last few times the concrete mix itself is always runny and not a normal thick consistency. Please advise if going here.
Very busy.  Friendly service.  Good food.    Gluten free buns are a bonus!

The workers on the evening shift on Wed are WONDERFUL! As soon as I walked in there, one of the employees, who was halfway across the restaurant, came over and asked us how we were doing. Very nice and upbeat, happy staff. Also, Selena was our server, and she was so sweet. Very nice happy atmosphere just brightened up my day. Oh and the burgers were as good as always! Keep doing what your doing Culver's because MAN you know how to run a restraunt well!
Burger was bland but fresh and hot. My son's mixer was all winner and the cheese curds are always delicious. Service was great and fast.
Drive through person should really speak up.. They totally trashed my order 4pm

Love the food, but never get the fork for the side salad I order… this has happened multiple times now. Something so simple, but prevents me from eating my meal properly. These guys need to pay attention to detail a bit more.

Food is always fresh and delicious and I enjoy the variety and portions for the price! Friendly and fast customer service and I rarely get a wrong order! I love the burgers, pretzel bites with cheese sauce, Fish sandwiches and turtle sundaes with the pecan pieces.  Oooh weeee!

This Culver's gave me a shake with a spoon, not a straw😵 Unfortunately, I didn't notice until I got ready to sip and latched onto a plastic straw.  I went to the drive thru and had to wait until I got home before I could enjoy my Raspberry Shake😵😵‍💫🥴😱
Shrimp is great! Check ✔️ your food before you leave. They forget stuff often. Like sauces for example. Love the food...
Every time we go the food is sloppily made and cold. The lines are super long at peak times.

Ordered a blackberry lemon cooler as part of a bigger $30+ order. My order (specifically blackberry) was repeated back to me twice to confirm.

Pulled up, paid - and was handed a partially filled cooler (more than an inch below the rim) that was pink.

‘I ordered blackberry, this isn’t the right color. Looks like strawberry?’

‘Yeah you ordered blackberry but we don’t have blackberries, it’s strawberry.’

No offer to refund, no apology. Just a shrug.

Grateful I’m not allergic to strawberry, but as it is a common allergy for people - very concerning.

I pointed out the allergy risk and was shrugged off again. ‘This isn’t what I ordered.’ *shrug*

Despite this being the closest location to our house we usually travel 10+ more minutes to other locations because the food (dry, overcooked, missing or wrong items) and service are so much better at other locations.

This experience sealed the deal for us avoiding this location regardless of convenience.
Good food. Decent prices. Highly recommended.
These kids must get top dollar!, Holy hell they stayed professional as usual even under pressure!

Went thru the drive thru. There was a misunderstanding about our order when we got to the window. Got it fixed and the young man gave my mom a senior discount. Didn't know they had that. Other than that everything else was okay.

I had a couple of bad experiences with food here. Even when I tried to give them another chance, they still seemed to mess up my order. They even messed up om my free meal. Even though they could not get the food right, they were very  hospitable people

Terrible service,  waited for over 25 minutes for 1 chix sandwiches & soggy fries.  Called the manager I don't think cared ?  No napkins.  I called before checking my food, found mushy not done fries.  Noticed in the bottom on bag ,a free combo card ..   So they already knew before giving me my food they were Terrible  !!  This use to be a great location,  not anymore..
I stopped in around 10:20am and the shake/custard machine wasn't ready. That was my only disappointment
Food tasted great but shortly after I got sick. Back and forth trips to the bathroom for a few hours.
Love the burgers. Fries not so much. Walleye sandwich was fishy and soggy. They forgot the burger for the kids meal. Peach crisp lacked real peach flavor and had no crisp.
Shared an excellent meal with my sister-in-law on her 80th birthday!

Not getting a bun top is disappointing.

Repeated poor experiences at this location have soured me on Culver's generally, which is a shame. It used to be reliably good.

Donna is phenomenal! Always makes 4 generations of my family welcome on a Sunday lunch. When my great-nephew doesn't want to eat, she tells him "one more bite" and he always listens to her and gives her a hug when we leave. She also keeps me Dad in line with a quick wit. She keeps us coming back!
I order 2 orders of the pretzels bits both were almost burnt we threw them out.  Need better help
Rude rude rude. 5 drinks only 1/2 full. Not mixed. Took 25 minutes to get the order right. Manager sucked also.. not compensated for the money I spent and didn't recieve

I placed a large office order in the drive through (6 people ordered) and only 1 meal was correct.  Our fish sandwich had none of the condiments other than tarter sauce, we had 2 orders of shrimp which I had ordered 4 cocktail sauces for and received zero, my value menu fries had to be given to a coworker because the extra order of fries never made it to the order ticket, and our double cheese burger with the works came as a double cheese on a bun and no condiments or toppings in sight.

I called the store to request to come pick up the cocktail sauces and toppings for the works burger and was told that they're super busy right now, could I come back in a couple hours... I repeated myself, explaining that I now had 2 coworkers now forced to eat dry shrimp and I've just had to cover the cost of the double cheese burger myself because it wasn't made as ordered.  The manager repeated that they're super busy and she could offer to remake the double cheese burger within the next couple days.  I asked if I could at least come pick up the cocktail sauce and was told again just how busy they were.  I UNDERSTAND HOW BUSY YOU WERE, I WAS JUST THERE TO PLACE AND PICK UP THE ORDER.  The manager offered the cocktail sauces at the time of the replacement cheese burger, but admitted it would be rather pointless at that time.

C'mon.... remaking a burger will upset the kitchen groove, I get it.  You're telling me you can't pull 4 cocktail sauces out and toss them in a bag so the guys have something to dip their shrimp in?  This is the simplest form of customer service, I place an order and you fill it.  I don't feel it's unreasonable to expect to be able to return to pick up a couple sauces so at least the $15 in shrimp will get eaten after being paid for.
The food is awesome,  the dining room is absolutely horrible, not a clean place inside, take your food and go.
Lisa and Faith as well as the team gave awesome friendly service . I really appreciate their hard work and appreciate them ! Thank you S.  Pennsylvania location
Didnt give us the 2 servings of cole slaw we asked for and paid for!
Food is good, prices are too high for what you get though... Decently friendly staff but they are not on that Chick-fil-A level.
As soon as we step in we are greeted and food is always cooked well.

Culver's is one of the best "fast foods". Yeah, there's a wait, but you get your order hot and fresh. Best and always soft burger buns. Cheese curds are a must! Best onion rings and chicken tenders too. Can't go wrong with custard either
Very poor services.  Waited for  25 mins  just to be told the kitchen never received my order.
Milkshake was served with multiple large holes in the cup

On 8/22/23 at 2:35pm I was over charged at the drive thru. I Ordered a 6 pc.Shrimp Meal  for $11.49 and received just 6 Shrimp and Fries.  I was charged $7.49 Shrimp, $2.49 Fries and a  $4. Value Basket. This totals $13.98. After 2 attempts from the young lady who tried to help me with the manager failed, I left. I was given a coleslaw, no dinner roll and no cost adjustment for the over charge. Manager told the girl the price is the same, but he needs to go back to Elementary School and relearn basic math. I was also not given back the pink receipt back with the Survey information.
Just disappointed! We are traveling with trailer and only the drive through is open, doors to restaurant locked. Could be staffing but won’t go out of our way to get off the expressway here again.

Order was wrong and missing items.  Drive through service was terrible, charged me for what I didn't order.  The only thing good about this culvers now is one of the managers who helped fix our issues.
Absolutely love the Cod meal but the last two times I was there they once, forgot my cheese curds, I substituted,  and once, forgot my cole slaw.  Also love the Strawberry -Mango Smoothie..
Ali demonstrated amazing customer service! Food was fresh and the team was so helpful in me navigating the menu as a first time customer. I will definitely be back!
